cs, in order to produce comprehensive national data of the highest standard.
The AIHW is an Australian Government [[statutory agency]] established under the ''Australian Institute of Health and Welfare Act 1987''. The Act contains very strong [[confidentiality]] protections for all data held, and requires the AIHW to publish two key biennial reports in alternate years: ''Australia’s health'' and ''Australia’s welfare''. Numerous other reports are produced each year, all of which are available free of charge on the AIHW website.<ref>[http://www.aihw.gov.au Australian Institute of Health and Welfare]</ref>
In 2016, the Australian Institute of Health and Welfare and the National Hospital Performance Authority merged.<ref>https://www.health.gov.au/internet/budget/publishing.nsf/Content/2014-2015_Health_PBS_sup2/$File/2014-15_Health_PBS_4.02_AIHW.docx</ref>
