'''Functional hypothalamic amenorrhea''' is a form of [[amenorrhea]]. It is caused by [[hypogonadism]] related to defective functioning of the [[hypothalamus]].<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Meczekalski B, Katulski K, Czyzyk A, Podfigurna-Stopa A, Maciejewska-Jeske M | title = Functional hypothalamic amenorrhea and its influence on women's health | journal = [[Journal of Endocrinological Investigation]] | volume = 37 | issue = 11 | pages = 1049–56 | date = November 2014 | pmid = 25201001 | pmc = 4207953 | doi = 10.1007/s40618-014-0169-3 }}</ref> It is one of the most common types of [[secondary amenorrhea]].<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Stárka L, Dušková M | title = [Functional hypothalamic amenorrhea] | language = Czech | journal = Vnitrni Lekarstvi | volume = 61 | issue = 10 | pages = 882–5 | date = October 2015 | pmid = 26486482 }}</ref>

