{{Infobox Political post |post = [[Ambassador]] |body = Pakistan to the United Nations |nativename = |insignia = State emblem of Pakistan.svg |insigniasize = 120px |insigniacaption = State emblem of Pakistan |department = [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Pakistan)]] |image = |alt = |incumbent = [[Maleeha Lodhi]] |incumbentsince = 6th February 2015 |style = Her Excellency Ambassador |residence = [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]] |nominator = [[Imran Khan]] |nominatorpost = [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]] |appointer = [[Arif Alvi]] |appointerpost = [[President of Pakistan]] |termlength = 3 years |inaugural = [[Patras Bokhari]] |formation = 1951 |last = |abolished = |succession = |deputy = Sheikh Nabeel Munir <small>Deputy Permanent Representative</small> |salary = |website = [http://www.pakun.org/the-mission.php Pakistan Mission – UN] }} '''Pakistan [[Ambassador to the United Nations]]''' or officially the '''Permanent Representative of Pakistan to the United Nations''' ({{lang-ur|{{nq|اقوام متحدہ میں پاکستان کا مستقل مندوب}}}}) is the diplomatic position representing [[Pakistan]] on all platforms of the United Nations ([[United Nations|UN]]) in [[New York City]]. Apart from the Pakistan Mission to the UN in New York, there is another Pakistan Mission based at the UNO office in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]].
The mission is usually headed by a career [[foreign service]] officer, but has historically been led by an eminent personalities from business, media, law and other areas and are usually political appointees. The current holder of the position is [[Maleeha Lodhi|Dr. Maleeha Lodhi]], prominent previous holders include [[Masood Khan]] and [[Muhammad Zafarullah Khan]].
